Rogue

Assignment #2
CIS*2500

Carter Bourette
Feb 18, 2016
0916638

——————————————————————————————————————————

Description:

A recreation of the classic game of Rogue. In
this spin off functionality is dumbed-down,
prepare for the coming of Assignment 3! Assignment
3 will encompass all your favourite aspects of Rougue.



Compilation:

This program is compiled without error in the
src folder using:

    "gcc -std=c99 -Wall main.c interface.c LinkedList.c -lncurses -I../include -o ../bin/A2"

The program can be compiled from the parent
folder (A2 folder) by typing "make".



Usage:

The program can be run by executing (from the
A2 folder):

    "./bin/A2 assets/input.txt"

Or by running the Makefile command
"make run" from the A2 folder.

    "make run"



Testing:

The program was tested without error using
the following files:

    - input.txt



Known Limitations:

The program is limited to the following design
specifications:

    - 9 rooms (exceeds specs by 3)
    - Line length of 150
    - Level file format (WIDTH ITEM ITEM ITEM)



References

Used LinkedList Library from personal development.
